A man was on Monday charged with attacking a Kiambu county government driver.The court was told Kelvin Njoroge attacked Geoffrey Muhia at Witeithie estate on the night of September 2. He allegedly stole a phone and cash from him and cut him with a panga.Njoroge, who was arrested on Friday last week at Witeithie, denied the charges. Thika chief magistrate Teresa Murigi released him on Sh3 million bond. The case will be mentioned on October 3. Njoroge linked the attackto another one on August 19, where county enforcement director Joseph Kangethe allegedly attacked him after he refused to carry potatoes to his wife s house.